Add sentinel-triggered test-build watcher for Mercury

- scripts/build-watch.sh: rebuild + docker compose up from the live working tree when a build_now sentinel exists; consumes the sentinel up front, flock-guarded, reuses the stable vault key from .env, logs to .build-logs/, reports FAIL to systemd
- scripts/systemd/authorclaw-build.{service,timer}: 1-min poll running as paul in the docker group
- scripts/systemd/README.md: install/check/uninstall steps
- scripts/deploy.sh: healthcheck polls /healthz instead of the now-auth-gated /api/health
- .gitignore: ignore build_now and .build-logs/
- docs/TODO.md: record the as-built sentinel approach on the Mercury-deploy item
